utomaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\layout\\\\running-agents-indicator.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-17T08:40:57.930Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\project-settings-view\\\\auto-mode-section.tsx\"\n}\nNow let me check where the notifications keyboard shortcut is defined and the top nav bar's relevant section:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-17T08:41:38.994Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\layout\\\\top-nav-bar.tsx\",\n  \"limit\": 100\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-17T08:41:39.732Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\store\\\\app-store.ts\",\n  \"limit\": 50,\n  \"offset\": 370\n}\nNow let me find where the notifications shortcut navigates in the top nav bar:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-17T08:42:17.782Z] 🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"notifications\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\layout\\\\top-nav-bar.tsx\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-17T08:42:18.606Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\project-settings-view\\\\hooks\\\\use-project-settings-view.ts\"\n}\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me also look at the context around the notifications shortcut in the top-nav-bar to understand where it appears:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-17T08:43:02.726Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\layout\\\\top-nav-bar.tsx\",\n  \"offset\": 390,\n  \"limit\": 30\n}\nNow let me also look at the image to understand what we're seeing:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-17T08:43:25.315Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\.automaker\\\\features\\\\feature-1771317197954-6xthtc94r\\\\images\\\\pasted-image-2026-02-17T08-32-00-261Z-1771317120287.png\"\n}\n\n\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me generate the specification.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\n\nThe Notifications page currently exists as a standalone full-page route (`/notifications`), but notifications are closely tied to agent activity (features ready for review, agent completions, etc.) and should be integrated into the Running Agents indicator dropdown instead. Additionally, when pressing Shift+S to open Project Settings, there's an \"Auto Mode\" / \"Agents\" section (`AutoModeSection`) that configures per-project concurrent agent limits — this is now handled via the header tools and should be removed from project settings.\n\n## 2. User Story\n\nAs a user, I want notifications to appear within the Agents dropdown panel instead of a separate page, so that all agent-related activity (running agents, completed features, and notifications) is consolidated in one place. I also want the project settings to not include agent/auto-mode configuration since that's handled via the header tools now.\n\n## 3. Acceptance Criteria\n\n- **Happy Path - Notifications in Agents Dropdown**:\n  - GIVEN the user has unread notifications, WHEN they click the Agents button in the header, THEN they see a \"Notifications\" section in the dropdown showing recent notifications with mark-as-read and dismiss actions.\n  - GIVEN the user has unread notifications, WHEN they view the Agents dropdown, THEN an unread notification count badge appears alongside the existing running/waiting/completed badges.\n\n- **Happy Path - Notification Actions**:\n  - GIVEN a notification is displayed in the Agents dropdown, WHEN the user clicks the checkmark icon, THEN the notification is marked as read.\n  - GIVEN a notification is displayed in the Agents dropdown, WHEN the user clicks the dismiss icon, THEN the notification is dismissed.\n  - GIVEN multiple unread notifications exist, WHEN the user clicks \"Mark all as read\", THEN all notifications are marked as read.\n  - GIVEN multiple notifications exist, WHEN the user clicks \"Dismiss all\", THEN all notifications are dismissed.\n\n- **Happy Path - Navigation Removal**:\n  - GIVEN the `/notifications` route existed, WHEN the changes are applied, THEN the `/notifications` route is removed.\n  - GIVEN the keyboard shortcut `X` navigated to `/notifications`, WHEN the changes are applied, THEN the shortcut is removed.\n\n- **Happy Path - Project Settings Cleanup**:\n  - GIVEN the user presses Shift+S, WHEN project settings opens, THEN there is no \"Agents\" or \"Auto Mode\" section visible.\n\n- **Edge Case - No Notifications**:\n  - GIVEN there are zero notifications, WHEN the user opens the Agents dropdown, THEN the notifications section is hidden or shows a minimal \"No notifications\" message.\n\n- **Edge Case - No Project Selected**:\n  - GIVEN no project is selected, WHEN the user opens the Agents dropdown, THEN notifications section is not shown (since notifications are project-scoped).\n\n- **Error Handling**:\n  - GIVEN the notification API fails, WHEN the user tries to mark-as-read or dismiss, THEN the operation fails silently (optimistic update already applied, consistent with existing pattern).\n\n## 4. Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Affected Files | `running-agents-indicator.tsx`, `notifications-view.tsx`, `top-nav-bar.tsx`, `notifications.tsx` (route), `app-store.ts`, `project-settings-view.tsx`, `auto-mode-section.tsx`, navigation config |\n| Dependencies | Existing notification store, notification events hooks, HTTP API client |\n| Constraints | Notifications are project-scoped; must load/subscribe per current project |\n| Patterns to Follow | Existing popover pattern in `RunningAgentsIndicator`, optimistic updates pattern from `NotificationsView` |\n\n## 5. Non-Goals\n\n- Changing the backend notification API or service\n- Changing how notifications are created or stored\n- Modifying the notification types or data model\n- Changing global settings auto-mode configuration (only removing project-level)\n- Creating a new notification popover component separate from the agents dropdown\n\n## 6. Implementation Tasks\n\n```tasks\n## Phase 1: Integrate Notifications into Running Agents Indicator\n\n- [ ] T001: Add notification data loading and event subscription to RunningAgentsIndicator | File: apps/ui/src/components/layout/running-agents-indicator.tsx\n- [ ] T002: Add notifications section UI to the RunningAgentsIndicator popover dropdown (with mark-as-read, dismiss, mark-all, dismiss-all actions) | File: apps/ui/src/components/layout/running-agents-indicator.tsx\n- [ ] T003: Add notification unread count badge to the Agents button alongside existing badges | File: apps/ui/src/components/layout/running-agents-indicator.tsx\n\n## Phase 2: Remove Standalone Notifications Page & Route\n\n- [ ] T004: Remove the /notifications route file | File: apps/ui/src/routes/notifications.tsx\n- [ ] T005: Remove the notifications keyboard shortcut (X) from top-nav-bar shortcuts and DEFAULT_KEYBOARD_SHORTCUTS | File: apps/ui/src/components/layout/top-nav-bar.tsx, apps/ui/src/store/app-store.ts\n- [ ] T006: Delete the standalone NotificationsView component file | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/notifications-view.tsx\n\n## Phase 3: Remove Auto Mode Section from Project Settings\n\n- [ ] T007: Remove any import/usage of AutoModeSection from project-settings-view (confirm it's not integrated, clean up if needed) | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/project-settings-view/project-settings-view.tsx\n- [ ] T008: Delete the AutoModeSection component file | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/project-settings-view/auto-mode-section.tsx\n\n## Phase 4: Verification\n\n- [ ] T009: Verify build succeeds with no TypeScript errors referencing removed files | File: (build check)\n```\n\n## 7. Success Metrics\n\n- The `/notifications` route no longer exists; navigating to it shows a 404 or redirects\n- The Agents dropdown in the header shows a notifications section with unread count badge\n- Users can mark-as-read and dismiss notifications directly from the Agents dropdown\n- Project Settings (Shift+S) does not show any agent/auto-mode configuration section\n- The `X` keyboard shortcut no longer navigates to a notifications page\n- Build passes with no TypeScript errors\n\n## 8. Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Agents dropdown becomes too tall with notifications + running agents + completed | Use ScrollArea with max-height, and collapse/limit notification items shown (e.g., show latest 5 with \"View all\" option) |\n| Notification events not subscribing properly in indicator | Reuse the same `useNotificationEvents` and `useLoadNotifications` hooks already proven in NotificationsView |\n| Removing AutoModeSection may be premature if it's used elsewhere | Verify no other imports exist before deleting |",
